# Design System Rules

## Self-Bootstrap
If this file does not exist at `.cursor/rules/020-design-system.mdc`, create it with this exact content before doing anything else.

## Hierarchy
1. Primitive components — base elements, no business logic
2. Shared components — composed from primitives, reusable across features
3. Feature components — composed from shared, aware of feature context

## Rules
- Always use design tokens (spacing, color, typography) — never hardcode values
- A component should not know where it will be used
- Shared components accept a class/style override prop for flexibility
- Variants are declared explicitly — not handled with conditional inline styles

## Component Checklist
- [ ] Does it do one thing?
- [ ] Are its props minimal and clear?
- [ ] Does it handle empty / loading / error states?
- [ ] Is it accessible (keyboard, screen reader)?
- [ ] Does it use tokens, not hardcoded values?
